Class UndefinedProgressMonitor

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
IProgressMonitorIF, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
public class UndefinedProgressMonitor
extends javax.swing.JDialog
implements IProgressMonitorIF

Dialog that shows the evolution of the execution of a ITask. If this ITask is a defined task (we know the number of steps it must do) it shows a progress bar. If it doesnt, progress bar is filling and emptying

azabala
